Yes, beautiful. I would like to
see what porcelain Americans make.

00:28:56.269 --> 00:28:57.839
Nothing there.

00:28:57.853 --> 00:29:00.353
Beautiful porcelain, isn’t it?

00:29:04.103 --> 00:29:10.052
What an idea. It’s really beautiful porcelain.

00:29:15.012 --> 00:29:18.857
Because in the shops you don’t find
any American porcelain anywhere.

00:29:18.890 --> 00:29:22.517
It’s all Chinese or something.

00:29:22.540 --> 00:29:25.040
So I wanted to know.

00:29:25.880 --> 00:29:28.380
But I didn’t find any American porcelain anywhere.

00:29:28.380 --> 00:29:30.880
I think they are not very much interested.

00:29:33.130 --> 00:29:39.028
Nor did I find any crystal, American crystal.

00:29:41.111 --> 00:29:43.611
I don’t think they make any. Do they?

00:29:43.611 --> 00:29:53.132
I don’t think so, Mother. I think most of Americans buy
Waterford crystal, made by the Irish, German, Yugoslav.

00:29:53.160 --> 00:29:56.391
They don’t have any crystal, no?

00:29:56.390 --> 00:29:59.991
And the, and the, this also,

00:30:00.002 --> 00:30:05.050
this they don’t make. But the, the
crockery you use, is from where?

00:30:05.080 --> 00:30:09.660
Mainly crockery that the most
people like is English.

00:30:09.674 --> 00:30:13.922
There are all kinds of Royal
Doulton, all that kind of thing.

00:30:13.952 --> 00:30:18.512
Americans, there are also some china,
but I really don’t know so much of that.

00:30:21.992 --> 00:30:26.938
I mean, they never had this in America?

00:30:26.974 --> 00:30:30.428
So what other hand-made things they do?

00:30:30.454 --> 00:30:32.954
I mean before they started this.

00:30:32.954 --> 00:30:35.454
They must be doing some handwork.

00:30:38.964 --> 00:30:41.738
Woodwork?

00:30:41.746 --> 00:30:45.236
That, that’s all right, that’s,
they are not Americans, in a way.

00:30:45.256 --> 00:30:48.770
But to what handwork they
must have done before.

00:30:50.270 --> 00:30:51.120
Can you say?

00:30:51.130 --> 00:30:55.766
Good carpenters, Mother. They are good carpenters
and they make nice interiors of houses,

00:30:55.782 --> 00:31:02.501
wood houses, wood floors, cupboards.
But they, they made a lot of …

00:31:02.532 --> 00:31:05.032
No, but I mean in decorativeness.

00:31:05.032 --> 00:31:07.129
What do you say?

00:31:07.159 --> 00:31:09.659
In decorativeness, what
Americans have been making?

00:31:09.659 --> 00:31:10.949
Sculptures.

00:31:10.949 --> 00:31:12.179
Sculptures?

00:31:12.179 --> 00:31:14.439
Yes, all plastic, Mother.

00:31:14.439 --> 00:31:16.739
No, but in olden days they must be making.

00:31:16.739 --> 00:31:17.666
Jewellery?

00:31:17.666 --> 00:31:19.839
Jewellery, they are best in the world.

00:31:19.839 --> 00:31:22.339
Is it?

00:31:22.339 --> 00:31:23.999
Yes, Mother. They are the
best in the world, Mother.

00:31:23.999 --> 00:31:28.169
Their designs are, they have the most
designs; Cartier, New York.

00:31:28.169 --> 00:31:29.139
Is it?

00:31:29.169 --> 00:31:30.649
Excellent jewellers.

00:31:30.649 --> 00:31:33.149
I didn’t find anywhere.

00:31:36.568 --> 00:31:42.469
Mother, we have to go in the market. We have
to do the market. It’s not far from the hall.

00:31:42.529 --> 00:31:45.029
No, no, what I am saying before all this started.

00:31:45.029 --> 00:31:50.197
Yes. Beautiful, exquisite [unclear]
glass stone You will find there.

00:31:50.228 --> 00:31:53.742
Glass made.

00:31:53.802 --> 00:31:56.392
Crockery they make? What, which one?

00:31:56.433 --> 00:31:57.442
They made before.

00:31:57.442 --> 00:31:58.432
Before, yeah

